Class CourseEntry

  • java.lang.Object
    • management.Entry
      • management.CourseEntry

  • public class CourseEntry
extends Entry
    The CourseEntry class stores all course entries that belong to a Module.

    It is an extension of the Entry class.

    Several Constructors are given, but only a few are useful. Use only Constructors that are marked as "useful". All other Constructors are used for test purposes.

    • Field Detail

      • courses

        private java.util.List<Course> courses
        A List of courses. Consists of string arrays with two entries: courseID, description, degree, type.

        course = Shorthand symbol description = name of the course degree = Bachelor, Master, ... obligatory = true: the course is necessary - false: the course is voluntarily

      • CourseEntry

        public CourseEntry(java.lang.String date,
           boolean classification,
           boolean approvalstatus,
           boolean declined,
           long entryID,
           java.lang.String title,
           int order,
           java.util.List<Course> courses)
        Creates a CourseEntry with given parameters. (Overloaded)

        Difference: multiple courses needed as parameter. Used to create an Entry from already loaded data.

        useful

        Parameters:
        version - The version of this Entry-extension. (Used to initialize the super class)
        date - The modification date. (Used to initialize the super class)
        classification - Should this entry go to Dezernat 2 ? (Used to initialize the super class)
        approvalstatus - Is this entry already approved ? (Used to initialize the super class)
        declined - Is it declined and needs to be rewritten again ? (Used to initialize the super class)
        entryID - This entry's ID. (Used to initialize the super class)
        title - The title of this entry. Used by the document creation as content title. (Used to initialize the super class)
        order - The order of this entry. (Used to initialize the super class)
        courses - A List of courses. Consists of string arrays with two entries: course and degree.

      • CourseEntry

        public CourseEntry(java.lang.String title,
           int order,
           java.util.List<Course> courses)
        Creates a CourseEntry with given parameters. (Overloaded)

        Is used to create new CourseEntries. e.g. a Module needs to be modified or is created from scratch. The super class is initialized with default values for new Entry.

        useful

        Parameters:
        title - The title of this entry. Used by the document creation as content title. (Used to initialize the super class)
        order - The order of this entry. (Used to initialize the super class)
        courses - A List of courses. Consists of string arrays with two entries: course and degree.
